In the latest incident on Monday evening, a bus was set alight in Makhaya. CAPE TOWN - Two Golden Arrow buses have come under attack in Khayelitsha over the past two days.In the latest incident on Monday evening, a bus was set alight in Makhaya.On Sunday, another bus was targeted.Golden arrow's brown Dyke-Beyer says: Golden Arrow can confirm one of our buses was set alight yesterday evening in Makhaya. We are monitoring our services very closely and will be avoiding certain parts of Khayelitsha. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)